ught I'd share this here in case you haven't had a chance to see it.  It's about some very groundbreaking changes that are happening with the experience system, which should be beneficial to all, especially classes with experience penalties.  It also outlines some additional experience modifiers for certain zones.  For example after the next patch, Solusek's Eye where we fought last night will have an additional 13% experience attached to each kill!  There is also additional experience the larger a group is, so it would've been that much more since we usually had a 5 person group.  Okay, before this gets to being another long Loralana novel, I'll give the links (the producer letter with all these changes is quite long itself)<br>
<br>
Everquest Caster's Realm<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com">eq.castersrealm.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Front page of where I found this<br>
<br>
Copy of Gordon Wrinn's letter on Caster's Realm<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3140">eq.castersrealm.com/viewa...ticle=3140</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Official Everquest Message Board post w/discussion of players<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/047840.html">boards.station.sony.com/e...47840.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Well, what can I say, this seems very exciting! Take care!<br>
<br>
Loralana Mystere<br>
29th level Enchanter<br>
<br>
P.S.  Some quick rough math shows me that even with the deaths, these changes would've given me personally about an additional half a bubble of experience for the evening in Solusek's Eye.  Not bad at all! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bthecounciloftwilight.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cashewribs>CashewRibs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/17/01 11:56:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Big changes to EQ</span><hr size=1> Yes, I too am excited about the exp change.  And I think this will make people just explore the world a bit more!  True, there's nothing like fighting in a zone that you know so well, like SK.  I think that's a great place for early 20s to level up into their late 20s.  But like all padawans, we need to spread our wings.  The dungeons seem a bit harder, thus EQ has realized since people haven't used them as much, we're now given an incentive to go there.  I just hope people don't flock to dungeons now, making them overcrowded.  Although there is a benefit.  We'll probably get more full groups, getting another bonus exp. and if you get into trouble, people can help you out (if they're nice).  But we must all remember, with all this exp. bonus, when we die, it will show significantly, but they have reiterated that we'll regain back the lost exp. that much faster this time around. Solusek's Eye to me is a great place to hunt for a bit.  There is a lot of cool items that are dropped that the Twilight can so use! <br>
<br>
So here's to benefitting from this exp. patch!!  Be safe and have fun!!<br>
<br>
&quot;We're not bound by the odds, we defy them.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cashew Nutty<br>
(I almost have 2 FIBS into 29, yippees!!)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukinvarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinvarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/17/01 3:43:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Big changes to EQ</span><hr size=1> I guess we'll find out after the patch today if people start flocking to the dungeons.  I know with being in Solusek so much lately, a large percentage of the people there have been high levels farming equipment to sell.  It'll be interesting to see if the population varies pre-patch and post-patch.  I've had a lot of fun in Solusek, and hope it doesn't get over run too much, but maybe enough to discourage the farmers (I can't say that without picturing a straw hat) from coming in and killing all the creatures that would otherwise give people like us experience.  Of course people just may want to stick with what they're comfortable with, where they'll get experience in a safe manner.  I doubt that Upper Guk or Befallen will lure away the tons of people that find Oasis so attractive, but you never know!  In any case, I see this as being a win-win situation, those that are still afraid of the dungeons will have less competition in the great outdoors, and the farmed dungeons will have people in them (gasp!) gaining experience!  Anyway, those are my thoughts on that.  I can't wait to see what the changes are, you can bet I'll be around tonight to find out!  Bye for now.<br>
<br>
Kinvarian Wolfkin<br>
27th season Ranger of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukinvarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinvarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/18/01 2:43:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Big changes to EQ</span><hr size=1> Well, after spending some time in Solusek yesterday after the patch, it was definitely not any more crowded than normal.  The highest amount of people I saw there yesterday was 13.  Perhaps this will change over the next few days or weeks, but so far it looks good.  As far as the experience changes go, I've noticed a big difference, and couldn't be happier.  Well, that's about my final thoughts on that, I think all these changes have been good ones.  See you all later!<br>
<br>
Kinvarian Wolfkin<br>
29th season Ranger of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm1.showMessage?topicID=49.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm1.showMessage?topicID=35.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=45.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm1.threadControl?topicID=45.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=45.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fthecounciloftwilightfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=45.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm2">Character Bios<option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm1">Got news?<option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm12">Oake's Treehouse<option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm7">Quest Questions and Answers<option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm3">Stories<option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm8">Item and Equipment Grab Bag<option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm9">Dear Santa...<option value="thecounciloftwilightfrm6">Agendas, Plans, and Pr